
===============================================================================
HELP FOR: hyper_objects
===============================================================================

SYNOPSIS:

- a number of objects related to hypersurfaces and junctions are provided
  with GRTensorIII

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objects Defined in the spacetime:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

eA              Null surface tangent for y^A (y^2)

eB              Null surface tangent for y^B (y^3)

Gnn             G{a b} n{^a} n{^b}

Gxn(dn)         G{a b} diff(xform{^a}, y{c}) n{^b}

k(up)           Null surface tangent (generator)

kdotk           k{a} k{^a}

kdotN           k{a} N{^a}

n(dn)           Normal vector (non-null)

N(dn)           Normal vector (null)

NdotN           N{a} N{^a}

Tnn             T{a b} n{^a} n{^b}

Txn(dn)         T{a b} diff(xform{^a}, y{c}) n{^b}

xform(up)       Surface defintions as x{^a}= f(y{^b})



-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objects Defined on the hyper-surface:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

K(dn,dn)        Extrinsic curvature (timelike/spacelike)

trK             Trace of K(dn,dn)

Ksq             K{a b} K{^a ^b}

C1GeqnRHS       R + epsilon (Ksq - trk^2)

C1Geqn          -2 epsilon G{i j} n{^i} n^j = C1GeqnRHS

C1Teqn          16 pi T{a b} n{^a} n{^b} = C1GeqnRHS

C2GeqnRHS       K{a ^b; b} - trK{,a}

C2Geqn(dn)      G{a b} diff(xform{^a}, y{c}) n{^b} = C2GeqnRHS

C2Teqn(dn)      8 pi T{a b} diff(xform{^a}, y{c}) n{^b} = C2GeqnRHS

sigma(dn,dn)    sigma{a b} surface stress-energy tensor (non-null surface)

C(dn,dn)        Extrinsic null curvature formed via N(dn)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objects Defined once join() has been used
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

S(dn,dn)        S{a b} stress energy-tensor (non-null surface)

j_null(dn)      Surface flux for null shell

mu_null         Density for null shell

p_null          Pressure of null shell


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SEE ALSO: hypersurf, join
